"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with the code is that it's trying to access columns 'x1' and 'x2' within the apply function on a DataFrameGroupBy object which is grouped by 'y'. However, the apply function is applied to each group separately, and the shift operation is performed within each group. But the code is trying to assign the result back to the original DataFrame. The shift operation will also result in NaN for the last row of each group because there is no next row to compare with.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n<df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n>df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1, fill_value=x['x1'].iloc[-1])) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1, fill_value=x['x2'].iloc[-1]))).reset_index(drop=True)\"\n}"